CatDescriptText: Cutline of related images published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 17, 1941, reads: "Louis Drills For Baer By Playing With Big Sparmate; Clicks Over Airways - Here's Heavyweight Champion Joe Louis nonchalantly skipping rope at his training near Washington where he is training for his fight with Buddy Baer May 23. in center the champ is playing medicine ball with a sparmate with his bare hands.  At the right he is shown giving a good broadcast over Station WINX. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Joe Louis jumping rope and another boxer punching heavy bag in ring, in front of crowd, Riverside Stadium, Washington DC
